4
5 chore(node-rewards-canister): RecurringSyncTask for updating registry and node metrics (#7239)
6
7 Changes:
8
9 - Syncing registry and metrics with RecurringSyncTask instead of custom
10 implementation
11 - Timer syncs registry and metrics every hr + 5 min (to fetch asap
12 metrics for yesterday)
13 - Simplified metrics syncing: Metrics manager does not handle retries
14 but relies on timer
15 - Added `last_day_synced` check to prevent computing rewards in case of
16 missing metrics
17

+7const SECS_PER_HOUR: u64 = 3600;üîó
+8üîó
+9// This offset makes sure that the first sync of the day happens at 00:05, times that guaranteesüîó
+10// All the subnets have collected metrics for the previous dayüîó
+11const SYNC_OFFSET: u64 = 5 * 60; // 5 minutes in secondsüîó
+12üîó
+13#[derive(Copy, Clone)]üîó
+14pub struct HourlySyncTask {üîó
+15 canister: &'static LocalKey<RefCell<NodeRewardsCanister>>,üîó
+16}üîó
+17üîó
+18impl HourlySyncTask {üîó

+20 Self { canister }üîó
+21 }üîó
+22üîó
+23 fn default_delay() -> Duration {üîó
+24 let now_secs = current_time().as_secs_since_unix_epoch();üîó
+25 let since_hour = now_secs % SECS_PER_HOUR;üîó
+26üîó
+27 // Target is delaying execution until the next hour plus SYNC_OFFSET.üîó
+28 let next_sync_target_secs = if since_hour < SYNC_OFFSET {üîó
+29 now_secs - since_hour + SYNC_OFFSETüîó
+30 } else {üîó
+31 now_secs - since_hour + SECS_PER_HOUR + SYNC_OFFSETüîó
+32 };üîó
+33üîó
+34 Duration::from_secs(next_sync_target_secs - now_secs)üîó
+35 }üîó
+36}üîó
+37üîó
+38impl RecurringSyncTask for HourlySyncTask {üîó
+39 fn execute(self) -> (Duration, Self) {üîó
+40 ic_cdk::futures::spawn_017_compat(async move {üîó
+41 match NodeRewardsCanister::schedule_registry_sync(self.canister).await {üîó
+42 Ok(_) => {üîó
+43 ic_cdk::println!("Successfully synced local registry");üîó
+44 match NodeRewardsCanister::schedule_metrics_sync(self.canister).await {üîó
+45 Ok(_) => {üîó
+46 ic_cdk::println!("Successfully synced subnets metrics")üîó
+47 }üîó
+48 Err(e) => {üîó
+49 ic_cdk::println!("Failed to sync subnets metrics: {:?}", e)üîó
+50 }üîó
+51 }üîó
+52 }üîó
+53 Err(e) => {üîó
+54 ic_cdk::println!("Failed to sync local registry: {:?}", e)üîó
+55 }üîó
+56 };üîó
+57 });üîó
+58üîó
+59 (Self::default_delay(), self)üîó
+60 }üîó
+61üîó
+62 fn initial_delay(&self) -> Duration {üîó
+63 Duration::from_secs(0)üîó
+64 }üîó
+65 const NAME: &'static str = "hourly_sync";üîó
+66}üîó

4
5 feat(node-rewards-canister): Compute rewards over single day for all node providers (#7071)
6
7 Modified the `get_rewards_calculation` API.
8 No external changes, as the API is not yet in use.
9
10 Changes include:
11 - Compute rewards for all node providers over a single day, instead of
12 calculating the full reward period for a single provider.
13 - Add detailed comments explaining the attributes in the rewards
14 calculation results.
15 - Move API type conversions to the appropriate module for better
16 organization.
17

5 fix(node-rewards-canister): Discard DayUtc type in favor of NaiveDate (#6981)
6
7 This introduces some breaking changes to the Node Rewards canister API,
8 however that's considered acceptable since nobody is calling it yet.
9
10 Changes:
11
12 - Removed completely `DayUtc` base custom type in favour of
13 `chrono::NaiveDate`
14 - Adapted DayUtc in API types to work with `chrono::NaiveDate`
15 - Adapted tests
16

chore(ICP_Ledger): FI-1845: Remove ICP ledger notify-method feature (#6717)
  • rs/node_rewards/canister/BUILD.bazel
1commit d161192b1376423686e5a826b7affb0da7bc868c
2Author: Mathias Bj√∂rkqvist <mathias.bjorkqvist@dfinity.org>
3Date: Fri Sep 26 12:36:09 2025 +0200
4
5 chore(ICP_Ledger): FI-1845: Remove ICP ledger notify-method feature (#6717)
6
7 Remove the `notify-method` feature from the ICP ledger canister. The
8 `notify` endpoint is still exported, but traps when called. Since many
9 consumers still expect the `ledger-canister_notify-method.wasm.gz` file,
10 this is still being built and uploaded to the CDN, but it is identical
11 to the `ledger-canister.wasm.gz` file. Subsequent ICP ledger suite
12 releases will include both (identical) files, and at some later point,
13 the `ledger-canister_notify-method.wasm.gz` will be removed.
14

4
5 chore: bump rust to 1.89 (#6758)
6
7 This PR bumps rust version to `1.89`. These changes were generated by:
8 * automatic `cargo fix --workspace --all-targets --keep-going ...`
9 * automatic `cargo clippy --fix ...` (It did fix some things that the
10 above command missed)
11 * Manually applied rustc
12 [`mismatched_lifetime_syntax`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/beta/nightly-rustc/rustc_lint/lifetime_syntax/static.MISMATCHED_LIFETIME_SYNTAXES.html)
13 fixes
14 * Manually applied clippy
15 [`cloned-ref-to-slice-refs`](https://rust-lang.github.io/rust-clippy/master/index.html#/cloned-ref-to-slice-refs)
16 * Had to add some `#[allow(dead_code)]` because the `const` values used
17 in `lazy_static!` weren't viewed as ever used. Left `//TODO:` to ask if
18 some of the parts that aren't used are needed
19 * Small manual patching of difference between
20 ```bash
21 bazel query 'kind("rust_library", //...) union kind("rust_binary", //...) union ("rust_test", //...)' > targets
22 bazel build --config=lint --target_pattern_file=targets
23 ```
24

28 Co-authored-by: Nicolas Mattia <nicolas.mattia@dfinity.org>

+23// ================================================================================================üîó
+24// VERSIONING SAFETY WARNINGüîó
+25// ================================================================================================üîó
+26//üîó
+27// This PerformanceBasedAlgorithm trait defines the core reward calculation interface.üîó
+28//üîó
+29// The trait methods in this module should NOT be modified directly as they serve as theüîó
+30// stable API contract for all reward calculation versions. Instead, new algorithm versionsüîó
+31// should be created by implementing this trait with different behavior, as demonstratedüîó
+32// by RewardsCalculationV1.üîó
+33//üîó
+34// This approach ensures:üîó
+35//üîó
+36// 1. **API Stability**: The trait interface remains consistent across versionsüîó
+37// 2. **Backward Compatibility**: Existing implementations continue to worküîó
+38// 3. **Version Isolation**: Each version can have its own calculation logicüîó
+39// 4. **Historical Reproducibility**: Past calculations remain verifiableüîó
+40//üîó
+41//üîó
+42// To create a new algorithm version:üîó
+43// 1. Create a new module (e.g., v2.rs)üîó
+44// 2. Implement the PerformanceBasedAlgorithm traitüîó
+45// 3. Override only the methods that need different behaviorüîó
+46// 4. Keep the same trait interface for compatibilityüîó
+47// ================================================================================================üîó

+106trait PerformanceBasedAlgorithm {üîó
+107 /// The percentile used to calculate the failure rate for a subnet.üîó

+111 /// Nodes with a failure rate below `MIN_FAILURE_RATE` will not be penalized.üîó

+113üîó

+117üîó
+118 /// The minimum rewards reduction for a node.üîó

+121 /// The maximum rewards reduction for a node.üîó

+124 /// From constant [NODE_PROVIDER_REWARD_PERIOD_SECONDS]üîó

+126 /// const SECONDS_IN_DAY: u64 = 86400;üîó

+129üîó
+130 fn validate_reward_period(from_day: &DayUtc, to_day: &DayUtc) -> Result<(), String> {üîó
+131 let today: DayUtc = current_time().as_nanos_since_unix_epoch().into();üîó
+132 if from_day > to_day {üîó
+133 return Err("from_day must be before to_day".to_string());üîó
+134 }üîó
+135 if to_day >= &today {üîó
+136 return Err("to_day_timestamp_nanos must be earlier than today".to_string());üîó
+137 }üîó
+138 Ok(())üîó
+139 }üîó
+140üîó
+141 fn calculate_rewards(üîó
+142 from_day: &DayUtc,üîó

+144 node_provider_filter: Option<PrincipalId>,üîó

+147 Self::validate_reward_period(from_day, to_day)?;üîó

+150 let mut total_rewards_per_provider = BTreeMap::new();üîó
+151 let mut daily_results = BTreeMap::new();üîó
+152üîó
+153 // Process each day in the reward periodüîó

+157üîó

+160 total_rewards_per_providerüîó

+172üîó

+174 total_rewards_xdr_permyriad,üîó

+178üîó
+179 fn calculate_daily_rewards(üîó

+186 let providers_rewardable_nodes = if let Some(provider_id) = node_provider_filter {üîó
+187 data_provider.get_provider_rewardable_nodes(day, provider_id)?üîó
+188 } else {üîó

+192üîó
+193 // Calculate failure rates for subnets and individual nodesüîó

+198üîó
+199 // Process each provider's nodesüîó

+208üîó
+209 Ok(DailyResults {üîó

+214üîó
+215 fn calculate_provider_rewards(üîó
+216 rewards_table: &NodeRewardsTable,üîó
+217 nodes_metrics_daily: &mut BTreeMap<NodeId, NodeMetricsDaily>,üîó
+218 rewardable_nodes: Vec<RewardableNode>,üîó
+219 ) -> NodeProviderRewards {üîó
+220 let mut provider_nodes_metrics_daily = BTreeMap::new();üîó
+221 for node in &rewardable_nodes {üîó

+224 }üîó

+227 let relative_nodes_fr: BTreeMap<NodeId, Decimal> = provider_nodes_metrics_dailyüîó

+235 let values: Vec<Decimal> = relative_nodes_fr.values().cloned().collect();üîó
+236 avg(&values).unwrap_or_default()üîó
+237 } else {üîó
+238 Decimal::ZEROüîó
+239 };üîó
+240üîó
+241 // Calculate performance multipliers based on failure ratesüîó
+242 // Assigned nodes use actual failure rate, unassigned nodes use extrapolated rateüîó
+243 let PerformanceMultiplierResults {üîó
+244 reward_reduction,üîó
+245 performance_multiplier,üîó
+246 } = Self::calculate_performance_multipliers(üîó
+247 &rewardable_nodes,üîó
+248 &relative_nodes_fr,üîó
+249 &extrapolated_fr,üîó
+250 );üîó
+251üîó
+252 // Calculate base rewards for each node based on region and node typeüîó
+253 // Handles special logic for Type3 nodes (grouped by country, with reduction coefficients)üîó
+254 let BaseRewardsResults {üîó

+256 base_rewards,üîó

+259üîó
+260 // Apply performance multipliers to base rewards to get final daily rewardsüîó
+261 let AdjustedRewardsResults { adjusted_rewards } = Self::apply_performance_adjustments(üîó
+262 &rewardable_nodes,üîó
+263 &base_rewards_per_node,üîó
+264 &performance_multiplier,üîó
+265 );üîó
+266üîó
+267 // Combine all calculated values into the final NodeProviderRewards structureüîó
+268 Self::build_provider_rewards_summary(üîó
+269 rewardable_nodes,üîó
+270 provider_nodes_metrics_daily,üîó
+271 extrapolated_fr,üîó
+272 reward_reduction,üîó
+273 performance_multiplier,üîó
+274 base_rewards_per_node,üîó
+275 adjusted_rewards,üîó
+276 base_rewards,üîó
+277 base_rewards_type3,üîó
+278 )üîó

+281 // ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------üîó
+282 // Calculate failure rates for subnets and individual nodesüîó
+283 // ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------üîó
+284 fn calculate_failure_rates(üîó
+285 daily_metrics_by_subnet: BTreeMap<SubnetId, Vec<NodeMetricsDailyRaw>>,üîó
+286 ) -> FailureRateResults {üîó
+287 fn calculate_daily_node_fr(num_blocks_proposed: u64, num_blocks_failed: u64) -> Decimal {üîó
+288 let total_blocks = Decimal::from(num_blocks_proposed + num_blocks_failed);üîó
+289 if total_blocks == Decimal::ZERO {üîó
+290 Decimal::ZEROüîó
+291 } else {üîó
+292 let num_blocks_failed = Decimal::from(num_blocks_failed);üîó
+293 num_blocks_failed / total_blocksüîó
+294 }üîó
+295 }üîó
+296üîó
+297 let mut result = FailureRateResults::default();üîó
+298üîó
+299 for (subnet_id, subnet_nodes_metrics) in daily_metrics_by_subnet {üîó
+300 let nodes_original_fr = subnet_nodes_metricsüîó
+301 .iter()üîó
+302 .map(|metrics| {üîó
+303 let original_fr = calculate_daily_node_fr(üîó
+304 metrics.num_blocks_proposed,üîó
+305 metrics.num_blocks_failed,üîó
+306 );üîó
+307 (metrics.node_id, original_fr)üîó
+308 })üîó
+309 .collect::<BTreeMap<_, _>>();üîó
+310 let nodes_fr = nodes_original_fr.values().cloned().collect::<Vec<_>>();üîó
+311 let failure_rates = nodes_fr.iter().sorted().collect::<Vec<_>>();üîó
+312 let index = ((nodes_fr.len() as f64) * Self::SUBNET_FAILURE_RATE_PERCENTILE).ceil()üîó
+313 as usizeüîó
+314 - 1;üîó
+315 let subnet_fr = *failure_rates[index];üîó
+316 result.subnets_fr.insert(subnet_id, subnet_fr);üîó
+317üîó
+318 for NodeMetricsDailyRaw {üîó
+319 node_id,üîó
+320 num_blocks_proposed,üîó
+321 num_blocks_failed,üîó
+322 } in subnet_nodes_metricsüîó
+323 {üîó
+324 let original_fr = nodes_original_fr[&node_id];üîó
+325 let relative_fr = max(Decimal::ZERO, original_fr - subnet_fr);üîó
+326üîó
+327 result.nodes_metrics_daily.insert(üîó
+328 node_id,üîó
+329 NodeMetricsDaily {üîó
+330 subnet_assigned: subnet_id,üîó
+331 subnet_assigned_fr: subnet_fr,üîó
+332 num_blocks_proposed,üîó
+333 num_blocks_failed,üîó
+334 original_fr,üîó
+335 relative_fr,üîó
+336 },üîó
+337 );üîó
+338 }üîó
+339 }üîó
+340 resultüîó

+342üîó
+343 fn calculate_performance_multipliers(üîó
+344 rewardable_nodes: &[RewardableNode],üîó
+345 relative_nodes_fr: &BTreeMap<NodeId, Decimal>,üîó
+346 extrapolated_fr: &Decimal,üîó
+347 ) -> PerformanceMultiplierResults {üîó
+348 let mut reward_reduction = BTreeMap::new();üîó
+349 let mut performance_multiplier = BTreeMap::new();üîó
+350üîó
+351 let calculate_rewards_reduction = |fr: Decimal| -> Decimal {üîó
+352 if fr < Self::MIN_FAILURE_RATE {üîó
+353 Self::MIN_REWARDS_REDUCTIONüîó
+354 } else if fr > Self::MAX_FAILURE_RATE {üîó
+355 Self::MAX_REWARDS_REDUCTIONüîó
+356 } else {üîó
+357 // Linear interpolation between MIN_REWARDS_REDUCTION and MAX_REWARDS_REDUCTIONüîó
+358 (fr - Self::MIN_FAILURE_RATE) / (Self::MAX_FAILURE_RATE - Self::MIN_FAILURE_RATE)üîó
+359 * Self::MAX_REWARDS_REDUCTIONüîó
+360 }üîó
+361 };üîó
+362üîó
+363 for node in rewardable_nodes {üîó
+364 let daily_fr_used = relative_nodes_früîó
+365 .get(&node.node_id)üîó
+366 .copied()üîó
+367 .unwrap_or(*extrapolated_fr);üîó
+368üîó
+369 let rewards_reduction = calculate_rewards_reduction(daily_fr_used);üîó
+370 let performance_mult = dec!(1) - rewards_reduction;üîó
+371üîó
+372 reward_reduction.insert(node.node_id, rewards_reduction);üîó
+373 performance_multiplier.insert(node.node_id, performance_mult);üîó
+374 }üîó
+375üîó
+376 PerformanceMultiplierResults {üîó
+377 reward_reduction,üîó
+378 performance_multiplier,üîó
+379 }üîó
+380 }üîó
+381üîó
+382 // ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------üîó
+383 // Calculate base rewards for each node based on region and node typeüîó
+384 // ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------üîó
+385 fn calculate_base_rewards_by_region_and_type(üîó
+386 node_rewards_table: &NodeRewardsTable,üîó
+387 rewardable_nodes: &[RewardableNode],üîó
+388 ) -> BaseRewardsResults {üîó
+389 fn get_monthly_rate(üîó
+390 rewards_table: &NodeRewardsTable,üîó
+391 region: &Region,üîó
+392 node_reward_type: &NodeRewardType,üîó
+393 ) -> (Decimal, RewardsCoefficientPercent) {üîó
+394 rewards_tableüîó
+395 .get_rate(region, &node_reward_type.to_string())üîó
+396 .map(|rate| {üîó
+397 let base_rewards_monthly = Decimal::from(rate.xdr_permyriad_per_node_per_month);üîó
+398 // Default reward_coefficient_percent is set to 80%, which is used as a fallback only in theüîó
+399 // unlikely case that the type3 entry in the reward table:üîó
+400 // a) has xdr_permyriad_per_node_per_month entry set for this region, butüîó
+401 // b) does NOT have the reward_coefficient_percent value setüîó
+402 let reward_coefficient_percent =üîó
+403 Decimal::from(rate.reward_coefficient_percent.unwrap_or(80)) / dec!(100);üîó
+404üîó
+405 (base_rewards_monthly, reward_coefficient_percent)üîó
+406 })üîó
+407 .unwrap_or((dec!(1), dec!(1)))üîó
+408 }üîó
+409üîó
+410 fn is_type3(node_type: &NodeRewardType) -> bool {üîó
+411 node_type == &NodeRewardType::Type3 || node_type == &NodeRewardType::Type3dot1üîó
+412 }üîó
+413üîó
+414 fn type3_region_key(region: &Region) -> String {üîó
+415 regionüîó
+416 .splitn(3, ',')üîó
+417 .take(2)üîó
+418 .collect::<Vec<&str>>()üîó
+419 .join(":")üîó
+420 }üîó
+421üîó
+422 let mut base_rewards = BTreeMap::new();üîó
+423 let mut base_rewards_type3 = BTreeMap::new();üîó
+424 let mut base_rewards_per_node = BTreeMap::new();üîó
+425üîó
+426 for node in rewardable_nodes {üîó
+427 let (base_rewards_monthly, coefficient) =üîó
+428 get_monthly_rate(node_rewards_table, &node.region, &node.node_reward_type);üîó
+429 let base_rewards_daily = base_rewards_monthly / Self::REWARDS_TABLE_DAYS;üîó
+430üîó
+431 base_rewardsüîó
+432 .entry((node.node_reward_type, node.region.clone()))üîó
+433 .or_insert((base_rewards_daily, base_rewards_monthly));üîó
+434üîó
+435 // For nodes which are type3* the base rewards for the single node is computed as the average of base rewardsüîó
+436 // on DC Country level. Moreover, to de-stimulate the same NP having too many nodes in the same country,üîó
+437 // the node rewards is reduced for each node the NP has in the given country. The reduction coefficient isüîó
+438 // computed as the average of reduction coefficients on DC Country level.üîó
+439 if is_type3(&node.node_reward_type) {üîó
+440 // The rewards table contains entries of this form DC Continent + DC Country + DC State/City.üîó
+441 // The grouping for type3* nodes will be on DC Continent + DC Country level. This group is used for computingüîó
+442 // the reduction coefficient and base reward for the group.üîó
+443 let region_key = type3_region_key(&node.region);üîó
+444üîó
+445 base_rewards_type3üîó
+446 .entry(region_key.clone())üîó
+447 .and_modify(üîó
+448 |(rates, coeffs): &mut (Vec<Decimal>, Vec<RewardsCoefficientPercent>)| {üîó
+449 rates.push(base_rewards_daily);üîó
+450 coeffs.push(coefficient);üîó
+451 },üîó
+452 )üîó
+453 .or_insert((vec![base_rewards_daily], vec![coefficient]));üîó
+454 }üîó
+455 }üîó
+456üîó
+457 let base_rewards_type3 = base_rewards_type3üîó
+458 .into_iter()üîó
+459 .map(|(region, (rates, coeff))| {üîó
+460 let nodes_count = rates.len();üîó
+461 let avg_rate = avg(rates.as_slice()).unwrap_or_default();üîó
+462 let avg_coeff = avg(coeff.as_slice()).unwrap_or_default();üîó
+463üîó
+464 let mut running_coefficient = dec!(1);üîó
+465 let mut region_rewards = Vec::new();üîó
+466 for _ in 0..nodes_count {üîó
+467 region_rewards.push(avg_rate * running_coefficient);üîó
+468 running_coefficient *= avg_coeff;üîó
+469 }üîó
+470 let region_rewards_avg = avg(&region_rewards).unwrap_or_default();üîó
+471üîó
+472 (üîó
+473 region,üîó
+474 (region_rewards_avg, nodes_count, avg_rate, avg_coeff),üîó
+475 )üîó
+476 })üîó
+477 .collect::<BTreeMap<_, _>>();üîó
+478üîó
+479 for node in rewardable_nodes {üîó
+480 let base_rewards_for_day = if is_type3(&node.node_reward_type) {üîó
+481 let region_key = type3_region_key(&node.region);üîó
+482üîó
+483 let (base_rewards_daily, _, _, _) = base_rewards_type3üîó
+484 .get(&region_key)üîó
+485 .expect("Type3 base rewards expected for provider");üîó
+486 base_rewards_dailyüîó
+487 } else {üîó
+488 let (base_rewards_daily, _) = base_rewardsüîó
+489 .get(&(node.node_reward_type, node.region.clone()))üîó
+490 .expect("base rewards expected for each node");üîó
+491 base_rewards_dailyüîó
+492 };üîó
+493üîó
+494 base_rewards_per_node.insert(node.node_id, *base_rewards_for_day);üîó
+495 }üîó
+496üîó
+497 let base_rewards_type3 = base_rewards_type3üîó
+498 .into_iter()üîó
+499 .map(üîó
+500 |(region, (daily_rewards, nodes_count, avg_rewards, avg_coefficient))| {üîó
+501 BaseRewardsType3 {üîó
+502 region,üîó
+503 nodes_count,üîó
+504 avg_rewards,üîó
+505 avg_coefficient,üîó
+506 value: daily_rewards,üîó
+507 }üîó
+508 },üîó
+509 )üîó
+510 .collect();üîó
+511üîó
+512 let base_rewards = base_rewardsüîó
+513 .into_iter()üîó
+514 .map(üîó
+515 |((node_reward_type, region), (daily_rewards, monthly_rewards))| BaseRewards {üîó
+516 node_reward_type,üîó

+518 monthly: monthly_rewards,üîó
+519 daily: daily_rewards,üîó
+520 },üîó
+521 )üîó
+522 .collect();üîó
+523üîó
+524 BaseRewardsResults {üîó
+525 base_rewards_per_node,üîó
+526 base_rewards_type3,üîó
+527 base_rewards,üîó

+531 fn apply_performance_adjustments(üîó

+539 let base_rewards_for_day = base_rewardsüîó
+540 .get(&node.node_id)üîó

+542üîó

+550üîó

+554 /// Build provider rewards summary using BTreeMap for consistency and better performanceüîó

+569 for node in rewardable_nodes {üîó

+621fn avg(values: &[Decimal]) -> Option<Decimal> {üîó
+622 if values.is_empty() {üîó

+625 Some(values.iter().sum::<Decimal>() / Decimal::from(values.len()))üîó
+626 }üîó

+185üîó

+188 node_good => dec!(0.05), // < 0.1üîó
+189 node_mid => dec!(0.35), // (0.35-0.1)/(0.6-0.1)*0.8 = 0.4üîó

+211üîó

+215üîó

+5# 2025-08-30: Proposal 138288üîó
+6üîó
+7http://dashboard.internetcomputer.org/proposal/138288üîó
+8üîó
+9## Addedüîó
+10üîó
+11* Add get_node_providers_rewards endpoint, to be used by the Governance to compute performance-based rewards.üîó
+12* Store rewards (including intermediate results) in stable memory for client retrieval.üîó
+13* Add get_node_provider_rewards_calculation endpoint to compute ongoing rewards and fetch historical ones.üîó
+14* Add get_historical_reward_periods endpoint to fetch historical reward periods and the providers rewarded.üîó
+15üîó
+16## Fixedüîó
+17üîó
+18* Fix rewards calculation algorithm to extrapolate with 0% failure rate node's performance for node providers with noüîó
+19 assigned nodes on a given day.üîó
20 * Replicated execution of the query endpoints `get_node_provider_rewards_calculation` and `get_historical_reward_periods`üîó
21 is disabled.üîó
